05/24/2022,748.1553 - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,07/13/2022,07/18/2022,Individual Standards Evaluated,High,Yes,A child was not taken promptly to receive medical care. ,"A follow up inspection was conducted at the operation (Inspection #3894687). Operation treatment director was interviewed regarding the plan for ensuring medical treatment is obtained timely. The operation will talk to children involved in the incident to determine if they need medical attention. If the child is in need of medical attention for an injury or illness the operation will immediately take the child to their PCP, Urgent Care or if it is after hours or the operation is unable to get to the child into the doctor's office they will take them to Cook's Children Emergency Room. "
